narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: this was an extremely valuable lesson in adapting to new environments, people, and research. It was tough for me personally, as the personalities in my labs were very different from my own in my first two rotations, but ultimately taught me about my own desires in research.

I learned lots of different laboratory skills, and learned about different areas of research. I also learned how to really "talk" about research, and how to give a good presentation about ones research.
Lab rotations were great, I greatly appreciate having the opportunity to rotate instead of picking a lab at the beginning of the year.
Lab work, experiencing lab cultures and research .

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I really liked rotations. I got a chance to try out different labs, using techniques I've never used before. I feel like they were a good length, as you got the chance to really learn what it would be like to be in each lab.
Knowing when we should submit our forms/ when are rotations will be more than one week ahead of time would be helpful.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! Three rotations were perfect, and by the end I had a good idea of what type of lab I wanted to join.
